This paper discusses the mathematical structure of machine learning methods, which is a fundamental topic in the field of machine learning. The paper also discusses the trade-offs between statistical and computational properties of ML methods, which is a common theme in many sub-fields of computer science. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
